At times, it can even bring upon horrific dangers that defy the human imagination.

9
00:02:49,060 --> 00:02:55,060
["Beware of Food You Pick Up Off the Ground"]

10
00:02:55,470 --> 00:02:58,220
Hmm... He's not eating again.

11
00:02:58,880 --> 00:03:02,620
Gin, Sadaharu doesn't have an appetite lately.

12
00:03:02,620 --> 00:03:04,690
He's hardly eaten anything for two days.

13
00:03:04,690 --> 00:03:06,580
He might not be feeling well.

14
00:03:06,880 --> 00:03:08,810
Maybe he's just on a diet.

15
00:03:09,260 --> 00:03:14,320
Males his age do silly things like that just so they can get girls.

16
00:03:14,320 --> 00:03:17,270
Sadaharu's not like that. He's the stoic type.

17
00:03:17,560 --> 00:03:21,930
The last time you said that, he was aroused over some female dog, remember?

18
00:03:21,930 --> 00:03:33,470
[Odd Jobs Gin]

19
00:03:22,300 --> 00:03:25,240
But he usually eats a lot. I'm worried.

20
00:03:25,690 --> 00:03:28,620
Maybe we should take him to the hospital.

21
00:03:28,620 --> 00:03:29,780
Leave him alone.

22
00:03:29,780 --> 00:03:32,270
He's tough. Sprinkle some salt for him to lick and he'll recover.

23
00:03:33,470 --> 00:03:36,180
[Kabukicho Animal Hospital]

24
00:03:36,700 --> 00:03:38,650
It seems there's a shadow in his stomach.

25
00:03:38,950 --> 00:03:41,330
Shadow? Is it something terrible?

26
00:03:41,330 --> 00:03:42,860
Who's behind this?

27
00:03:42,860 --> 00:03:45,770
Is it a shadow ninja, of the Tokugawa...or the Yagyu?

28
00:03:45,770 --> 00:03:49,180
No, not Tokugawa shadows. There's something in his stomach.

29
00:03:49,630 --> 00:03:51,590
Does he have an illness?!

30
00:03:51,590 --> 00:03:52,920
Is Sadaharu sick?!

31
00:03:52,920 --> 00:03:53,990
Will he recover?!

32
00:03:53,990 --> 00:03:55,310
He will recover, won't he?!

33
00:03:55,310 --> 00:03:57,180
Calm down.

34
00:03:57,180 --> 00:04:00,760
He's not sick. There's a foreign object in his stomach.

35
00:04:00,760 --> 00:04:01,760
Foreign object?

36
00:04:01,760 --> 00:04:06,190
Yes. Did you make Sadaharu eat anything odd?

37
00:04:06,190 --> 00:04:09,390
Huh? We haven't fed him anything except basic dog food.

38
00:04:09,390 --> 00:04:09,990
I see.

39
00:04:09,990 --> 00:04:13,130
Then he probably ate something off the ground when you took him for a walk.

40
00:04:13,450 --> 00:04:17,880
Dogs put unbelievable things in their mouths when their owners aren't looking.

41
00:04:18,210 --> 00:04:21,400
Especially since Sadaharu is a large breed, anything can go in.

42
00:04:21,400 --> 00:04:22,790
You need to be careful.

43
00:04:23,280 --> 00:04:26,220
So, this is the shadow.

44
00:04:27,220 --> 00:04:30,970
What could this be? I can't really tell.

45
00:04:31,770 --> 00:04:35,470
Anyway, I'll get him to vomit it out. That'll make him better in no time.

46
00:04:35,470 --> 00:04:37,370
No! Never mind!

47
00:04:37,370 --> 00:04:38,410
Huh? Why?

48
00:04:38,410 --> 00:04:39,760
No, it's because, you know!

49
00:04:39,760 --> 00:04:42,110
If all we have to do it make him vomit, we can do it ourselves.

50
00:04:42,110 --> 00:04:43,740
We're...going home.

51
00:04:43,740 --> 00:04:47,060
No, if it gets stuck in his throat as he vomits it out, it could be trouble.

52
00:04:47,490 --> 00:04:51,230
And depending on the situation, he might require surgery.

53
00:04:51,230 --> 00:04:52,450
We can manage!

54
00:04:52,450 --> 00:04:55,400
We're good at slitting our bellies. We're samurai, you know.

55
00:04:55,400 --> 00:04:56,740
No, not yours.

56
00:04:56,740 --> 00:05:00,170
No, really, it's all right. Just let us go. Don't call the police.

57
00:05:00,450 --> 00:05:01,210
The police?

58
00:05:03,440 --> 00:05:05,920
What're you doing? Hurry and come with us, Sadaharu!

59
00:05:05,920 --> 00:05:07,210
Do you want to be caught?

60
00:05:12,860 --> 00:05:14,050
It's coming out of his mouth!

61
00:05:14,050 --> 00:05:15,220
Gin, from his mouth.

62
00:05:15,380 --> 00:05:16,160
Push it back in!

63
00:05:16,160 --> 00:05:17,750
Sadaharu, open wide.

64
00:05:27,790 --> 00:05:30,900
For now, there doesn't seem to be anything else.

65
00:05:30,900 --> 00:05:33,700
But to be safe, they say he should stay overnight at the hospital.

66
00:05:34,110 --> 00:05:35,860
I see.

67
00:05:35,860 --> 00:05:39,460
I'm worried, so is it okay if I stay with Sadaharu overnight?

68
00:05:39,870 --> 00:05:41,370
Oh, okay.

69
00:05:44,790 --> 00:05:47,160
Why're they so tired?

70
00:05:48,170 --> 00:05:49,610
If it isn't Leader...

71
00:05:50,420 --> 00:05:51,960
Huh? Zura?

72
00:05:51,960 --> 00:05:53,490
Not Zura. Katsura.

73
00:05:53,840 --> 00:05:55,430
What're you doing here?

74
00:05:55,820 --> 00:05:58,410
Don't tell me Sir Sadaharu is not well?

75
00:05:58,460 --> 00:06:02,180
Not as sick as your mind. Don't worry.

76
00:06:02,180 --> 00:06:03,930
I see, I'm glad to hear that.

77
00:06:03,930 --> 00:06:05,720
Zura, what brings you here?

78
00:06:05,720 --> 00:06:09,520
Did you come to an animal hospital because regular hospitals won't touch you?

79
00:06:09,520 --> 00:06:12,260
No, Elizabeth's been lacking energy.

80
00:06:12,500 --> 00:06:14,640
I came here hoping to have her looked at.

81
00:06:15,160 --> 00:06:17,870
The X-rays showed a disturbing shadow.

82
00:06:17,870 --> 00:06:19,970
No, it's just an old man.

83
00:06:19,970 --> 00:06:24,070
Seems she ate something that looked like an old man off the ground during our walk.

84
00:06:24,070 --> 00:06:26,230
No, you're the one who picked up the old man, I bet.

85
00:06:26,690 --> 00:06:31,200
So that's why she'll be having an operation to remove the old man soon.

86
00:06:31,450 --> 00:06:34,400
Taking out the old man means the whole body.

87
00:06:34,400 --> 00:06:37,110
It's no wonder I thought she was behaving strangely.

88
00:06:37,330 --> 00:06:39,880
When I go near her, she smells of aging body odor.

89
00:06:39,880 --> 00:06:42,200
Hey, don't deny the truth.

90
00:06:42,200 --> 00:06:44,560
What you were keeping as a pet is just an old man.

91
00:06:45,460 --> 00:06:46,560
Well,

92
00:06:46,560 --> 00:06:50,090
it's a good thing neither was life-threatening.

93
00:06:50,510 --> 00:06:52,520
Yours is threatened.

94
00:06:52,520 --> 00:06:57,060
After all, you always want to have your pet smiling at your side.

95
00:06:57,370 --> 00:06:59,120
That's true.

96
00:07:00,630 --> 00:07:05,180
I did everything I could, but he was, after all, an old dog.

97
00:07:05,620 --> 00:07:09,160
I don't think his body can withstand any more treatment.

98
00:07:09,160 --> 00:07:10,570
I see.

99
00:07:10,570 --> 00:07:14,260
Kintaro...looks like I won't be able to take him to my Dad.

100
00:07:14,290 --> 00:07:16,600
Is your Father's condition that bad?

101
00:07:16,980 --> 00:07:19,640
Yes. Seems he's not going to make it, either.

102
00:07:19,970 --> 00:07:23,600
Imagine a pet dog and its owner falling ill at the same time.

103
00:07:23,600 --> 00:07:28,400
I see. Your father was really fond of Kintaro.

104
00:07:28,860 --> 00:07:30,530
An old man and his old dog.

105
00:07:30,820 --> 00:07:35,410
They both lost many things, until all that was left at the end was their friendship.

106
00:07:35,750 --> 00:07:39,260
Those fools, are they planning to die together as well?

107
00:07:39,860 --> 00:07:43,090
Doctor, I've got to go see my Dad.

108
00:07:43,090 --> 00:07:44,930
Please look after Kintaro.

109
00:07:44,930 --> 00:07:48,700
Please see to it that he passes on peacefully.

110
00:07:49,270 --> 00:07:53,260
Sorry... Kintaro, I won't say good-bye.

111
00:07:54,430 --> 00:07:56,010
Thanks.

112
00:08:31,540 --> 00:08:33,280
I can't fall asleep.

113
00:08:57,200 --> 00:08:58,400
Zura?

114
00:08:58,400 --> 00:09:01,260
What, are you trying to get in my way by sleeping there?

115
00:09:01,450 --> 00:09:02,770
Huh? No.

116
00:09:04,060 --> 00:09:06,580
I was having a bit of trouble falling asleep.

117
00:09:06,580 --> 00:09:09,220
Here there's a breeze and it seemed like a good place to sleep.

118
00:09:12,770 --> 00:09:16,010
That's true. I'll crash here, too.

119
00:09:28,870 --> 00:09:35,320
I'm sure he wanted his master to be at his side when he dies, not us.

120
00:09:35,920 --> 00:09:37,390
Who knows?

121
00:09:37,420 --> 00:09:38,930
I heard it from the doctor.

122
00:09:39,220 --> 00:09:43,860
It's almost a miracle that he's still alive despite being ravaged to such an extent by disease.

123
00:09:45,230 --> 00:09:50,430
This animal is apparently a loyal dog that supported his master who lived alone for all these years.

124
00:09:51,050 --> 00:09:54,020
He nestled up next to a stubborn old man

125
00:09:54,020 --> 00:09:59,170
who wouldn't even have anything to do with his own children after his wife died.

126
00:09:59,710 --> 00:10:01,500
He hung on until he was this ragged.

127
00:10:02,430 --> 00:10:04,640
When the old man collapsed,

128
00:10:04,640 --> 00:10:07,250
it seems he just flopped down as if to say his job had ended.

129
00:10:07,630 --> 00:10:12,060
No, maybe he is trying to follow his master into the afterlife.

130
00:10:13,340 --> 00:10:18,150
If that's the case, then maybe this is what he wanted.  This tiny samurai.

131
00:10:20,090 --> 00:10:25,010
Zura, that's why they send you to the animal hospital.

132
00:10:25,010 --> 00:10:25,820
What?

133
00:10:25,820 --> 00:10:26,650
I've made up my mind.

134
00:10:26,650 --> 00:10:29,420
I'm going to let this dog see the old man, after all.

135
00:10:30,220 --> 00:10:32,250
Wait, Leader. What're you talking about?

136
00:10:32,630 --> 00:10:34,910
You plan to take a dog in this condition with you?

137
00:10:34,910 --> 00:10:36,310
It can't wait.

138
00:10:36,310 --> 00:10:38,990
You're the only ones who'd be happy that he died

139
00:10:38,990 --> 00:10:41,170
all by himself in a place like this and became a noble tale.

140
00:10:41,170 --> 00:10:42,640
Have you forgotten?

141
00:10:42,640 --> 00:10:46,140
We can try to get them together, but the old man is on the brink of death himself.

142
00:10:46,140 --> 00:10:49,630
That's why I'm sure he's hoping to see each other, too.

143
00:10:49,630 --> 00:10:52,700
Hope to see him? He's already lost consciousness.

144
00:10:52,700 --> 00:10:54,790
It's all he can do just to breathe.

145
00:10:54,790 --> 00:10:56,760
He has no strength left.

146
00:10:57,220 --> 00:10:58,720
The doctor said so himself.

147
00:10:58,720 --> 00:11:00,880
Instead of needlessly making him suffer, let him peacefully...

148
00:11:06,130 --> 00:11:07,600
You...you're...

149
00:11:10,990 --> 00:11:14,130
Does it...mean that much to you?

150
00:11:14,770 --> 00:11:19,680
When a dog is ragged, and writhes in agony, desperately trying live a long life,

151
00:11:19,680 --> 00:11:23,470
the reason why he won't leave his master's side is obvious.

152
00:11:24,870 --> 00:11:27,910
It's because he wants to stay at his master's side forever.

153
00:11:28,490 --> 00:11:30,920
It's obviously because he doesn't want to leave.

154
00:11:31,320 --> 00:11:34,350
Then there's just one final thing we can do for this dog.

155
00:11:38,420 --> 00:11:39,920
I see.

156
00:11:39,920 --> 00:11:43,840
Little Mr. Samurai, I have underestimated you.

157
00:11:44,490 --> 00:11:50,330
A true samurai does not die for his beliefs. He lives for his beliefs, doesn't he?

158
00:11:50,730 --> 00:11:51,790
Okay!

159
00:11:51,790 --> 00:11:53,470
Let's head to where the old man is.

160
00:11:54,010 --> 00:11:55,470
Like hell I will!

161
00:11:59,240 --> 00:12:02,510
After eighteen years of suffering while sealed in by that despicable old man, finally...

162
00:12:02,510 --> 00:12:05,090
Finally, the chains have rotted off!

163
00:12:05,380 --> 00:12:07,850
The time for the resurrection of the King of Terror has come.

164
00:12:10,030 --> 00:12:13,520
Earth has come to an...

165
00:12:13,520 --> 00:12:18,060
Uh-oh, it hurts... Call an ambulance!

166
00:12:28,600 --> 00:12:32,060
[18 Years Prior]

167
00:12:28,930 --> 00:12:31,450
We go back in time eighteen years.

168
00:12:32,210 --> 00:12:34,690
From beyond the far reaches of the vast Universe,

169
00:12:35,050 --> 00:12:38,920
a frightful beam bringing disaster is approaching Earth.

170
00:12:50,120 --> 00:12:51,780
Parasite X.

171
00:12:52,080 --> 00:12:55,350
Feared as the "Planet Eater."

172
00:12:59,460 --> 00:13:02,960
X splits into infinite beams, raining down on the planet.

173
00:13:03,820 --> 00:13:06,010
Parasitically attaching to all life forms,

174
00:13:06,010 --> 00:13:08,250
it controls the central nervous system

175
00:13:08,250 --> 00:13:11,440
and manipulates its hosts' genes, evolving incredibly quickly,

176
00:13:11,440 --> 00:13:14,850
to create a powerful invasion force in the blink of an eye.

177
00:13:15,550 --> 00:13:21,590
Every planet invaded by X is left with a huge scar, as though torn off by a huge jaw.

178
00:13:22,610 --> 00:13:24,590
This is how they got the name "Planet Eaters."

179
00:13:27,470 --> 00:13:31,760
Earth.  Looks like quite a lovely planet.

180
00:13:32,570 --> 00:13:38,150
I tremble with excitement when I think of sinking my fangs into such a juicy planet.

181
00:13:39,630 --> 00:13:44,090
So, which creature should I attach myself to this time?

182
00:13:44,640 --> 00:13:47,810
Looks easy, so this time, I'll go with my eyes closed.

183
00:13:48,270 --> 00:13:51,550
Whatever happens, I'll probably be fine.

184
00:14:00,140 --> 00:14:03,430
I've entered a mongrel that almost died in its mother's womb.

185
00:14:06,500 --> 00:14:08,000
Idiot! I'm an idiot!

186
00:14:08,000 --> 00:14:09,710
Why did I get so carried away like that!

187
00:14:09,710 --> 00:14:11,770
With my eyes closed!

188
00:14:12,670 --> 00:14:17,180
Even my senpai told me the real climb begins just before the summit.

189
00:14:17,410 --> 00:14:20,880
As a result, I was cooped up in a dog house for eighteen years,

190
00:14:20,880 --> 00:14:23,320
spending peaceful days without being able to start on world conquest.

191
00:14:23,630 --> 00:14:25,990
Even then, though, I tried so hard.

192
00:14:25,990 --> 00:14:27,780
Fiddling around with the genes and such, you know?

193
00:14:27,780 --> 00:14:29,220
I tried to evolve, you know?!

194
00:14:30,410 --> 00:14:31,800
But in the end,

195
00:14:32,490 --> 00:14:34,910
all I could do was learn to do the front raise on a bar!

196
00:14:35,530 --> 00:14:38,510
As a final measure, I waited for the old man to die,

197
00:14:38,510 --> 00:14:40,820
but just when I thought I was finally free...

198
00:14:43,170 --> 00:14:44,990
My life reached its limit, as well.

199
00:14:45,910 --> 00:14:47,200
How cruel!

200
00:14:47,200 --> 00:14:49,850
Is there no god or King of Terror in this world?!

201
00:14:49,850 --> 00:14:51,940
All I've ever done is a front raise.

202
00:14:51,940 --> 00:14:53,430
I haven't even learned the glider yet!

203
00:14:53,430 --> 00:14:55,480
Give me back my life!

204
00:14:56,120 --> 00:14:59,920
So what happened is, you attempted to take over the Earth, but failed,

205
00:14:59,920 --> 00:15:02,220
and you were kept as the old man's pet this whole time?

206
00:15:02,220 --> 00:15:04,290
Then the reason you desperately tried to live a long life

207
00:15:04,290 --> 00:15:07,310
wasn't because you wanted to stay by the old man's side and support him, but...

208
00:15:07,310 --> 00:15:08,690
...to conquer the Earth.

209
00:15:09,010 --> 00:15:12,910
I waited vigilantly for the old man to die so I'd be freed from that stupid doghouse.

210
00:15:13,280 --> 00:15:14,470
Excuse me.

211
00:15:14,510 --> 00:15:15,300
Yes?

212
00:15:15,300 --> 00:15:18,430
Nuke this Amanto in the microwave and make a hot dog out of him.

213
00:15:18,430 --> 00:15:19,360
Nooo!

214
00:15:19,910 --> 00:15:21,700
I'm sick of this.

215
00:15:21,700 --> 00:15:24,360
My motivation's down. I'm going home.

216
00:15:24,360 --> 00:15:25,890
Now, wait, Leader.

217
00:15:25,890 --> 00:15:28,680
It's true there's nothing to be gained by helping this dog.

218
00:15:28,990 --> 00:15:32,380
But I'm sure the old man wants to see this dog, despite what it is.

219
00:15:32,830 --> 00:15:34,490
We should finish what we started.

220
00:15:34,490 --> 00:15:36,580
What've we got to lose by letting them see each other?

221
00:15:37,570 --> 00:15:38,950
Planet Eater...

222
00:15:38,950 --> 00:15:43,120
You've done a whole lot of evil. At least before you die...

223
00:15:43,120 --> 00:15:44,350
I've finally found you!

224
00:15:44,890 --> 00:15:46,430
What's going on?

225
00:15:46,930 --> 00:15:50,390
[18 Years Prior]

226
00:15:47,180 --> 00:15:50,020
We go back in time eighteen years.

227
00:15:50,510 --> 00:15:53,450
From beyond the far reaches of the vast Universe,

228
00:15:53,450 --> 00:15:57,070
an intense celestial light is approaching Earth.

229
00:16:07,300 --> 00:16:12,680
Parasite Z, revered as the Planet Pukers.

230
00:16:15,720 --> 00:16:19,220
Z splits into infinite beams, raining down on the planet.

231
00:16:20,250 --> 00:16:24,730
Parasitically attaching to any life form,

232
00:16:24,730 --> 00:16:27,640
they evolve incredibly quickly, exterminating the Planet Eaters and saving planets.

233
00:16:27,640 --> 00:16:31,730
They are, so to speak, the Planet Eaters' counterbalancing force-the allies of good.

234
00:16:32,840 --> 00:16:40,280
When Z saves a planet, it leaves covered in the vomit of its host as it is expelled.

235
00:16:41,060 --> 00:16:43,230
This is how they got the name "Planet Pukers."

236
00:16:44,630 --> 00:16:45,770
Earth.

237
00:16:46,190 --> 00:16:49,980
So the Planet Eaters are trying to eat away this beautiful planet.

238
00:16:51,670 --> 00:16:53,670
We must never allow that to happen.

239
00:16:53,890 --> 00:16:57,810
We will protect this planet without fail and cover it with vomit!

240
00:16:59,660 --> 00:17:03,660
But the question is, what animal shall we counter with?

241
00:17:04,820 --> 00:17:07,440
Looks easy, so this time, we'll go with our eyes half-opened.

242
00:17:07,900 --> 00:17:10,140
Whatever happens, it'll be fine.

243
00:17:14,650 --> 00:17:18,040
Planet Eater... I've finally found the last one of you.

244
00:17:19,300 --> 00:17:23,810
I will...kill you for sure!

245
00:17:24,200 --> 00:17:27,110
What's that? More strange creatures?

246
00:17:27,110 --> 00:17:28,060
That's...

247
00:17:28,060 --> 00:17:29,310
The Planet Pukers!

248
00:17:29,310 --> 00:17:31,430
Charge!

249
00:17:35,510 --> 00:17:39,510
[Oedo Hospital]

250
00:17:36,260 --> 00:17:38,620
I see. Poor Kintaro.

251
00:17:39,860 --> 00:17:45,430
He supported Dad for so long, but I couldn't be there when he dies.

252
00:17:46,240 --> 00:17:48,610
With Dad in this condition, it can't be helped.

253
00:17:48,940 --> 00:17:52,560
Besides, Dad's the one who most wanted to be there when that dog dies.

254
00:17:52,940 --> 00:17:54,540
He was so fond of him.

255
00:17:54,760 --> 00:17:57,700
Not to worry. They'll meet again in the afterlife.

256
00:17:57,700 --> 00:17:59,260
Hey, that's imprudent.

257
00:17:59,420 --> 00:18:01,800
You guys are stressing too much.

258
00:18:02,260 --> 00:18:04,430
You're exhausted because you've been tending to Dad all this time.

259
00:18:04,430 --> 00:18:05,570
Why don't you take a break?

260
00:18:06,110 --> 00:18:08,100
Looks like Dad will be okay for a while.

261
00:18:08,470 --> 00:18:09,750
Are you sure you'll be okay?

262
00:18:10,240 --> 00:18:13,020
Don't worry, don't worry. I'll keep a close watch.

263
00:18:13,470 --> 00:18:14,570
Okay, I'm counting on you.

264
00:18:15,080 --> 00:18:16,390
Alrighty.

265
00:18:27,500 --> 00:18:29,190
This isn't getting anywhere.

266
00:18:29,530 --> 00:18:32,680
What are they? Why're they attacking us?

267
00:18:33,070 --> 00:18:34,430
Planet Pukers...

268
00:18:34,430 --> 00:18:37,480
They're parasites that drive out Planet Eaters like me and protect planets.

269
00:18:37,480 --> 00:18:39,400
Quickly, quickly, get away.

270
00:18:39,400 --> 00:18:41,310
If they catch me, I'll be eliminated.

271
00:18:41,450 --> 00:18:43,010
I had no idea.

272
00:18:43,010 --> 00:18:46,120
I wouldn't have believed that cats and dogs

273
00:18:46,120 --> 00:18:47,690
battled over the fate of the world since ancient times.

274
00:18:47,690 --> 00:18:49,010
No, that's not how it is.

275
00:18:49,010 --> 00:18:52,540
It's just coincidence that I parasitically attached myself to a dog, and they attached to cats.

276
00:18:52,540 --> 00:18:54,930
What should I do?

277
00:18:55,310 --> 00:18:58,130
Dogs...and cats... Both are difficult to forsake.

278
00:18:58,570 --> 00:19:01,420
They're both cuddly balls of flesh and fluffy soft.

279
00:19:02,120 --> 00:19:03,520
Oh...what should I do?

280
00:19:03,800 --> 00:19:06,430
I don't' want either of them to disappear.

281
00:19:06,430 --> 00:19:08,290
Hey, are you even listening?!

282
00:19:08,290 --> 00:19:10,900
All right, I'll make a peace offering.

283
00:19:10,900 --> 00:19:12,370
They're both cuddly balls of flesh-

284
00:19:12,370 --> 00:19:14,110
if they discuss things, they should reach an understanding.

285
00:19:14,110 --> 00:19:17,090
Hey, why're you wasting time talking. Hurry and run.

286
00:19:17,090 --> 00:19:19,640
Listen to me, courageous cuddly balls of flesh.

287
00:19:19,640 --> 00:19:22,310
We have no intention of conquering Earth.

288
00:19:22,630 --> 00:19:26,560
Even without your help, this dog is at the end of his life!

289
00:19:26,740 --> 00:19:30,320
However, we want to let his owner see him once before he dies.

290
00:19:30,580 --> 00:19:33,930
As those who are also of flesh and blood, I'm sure you can understand!

291
00:19:33,930 --> 00:19:35,850
We're strays!

292
00:19:35,850 --> 00:19:38,350
Planet Eater! You came to conquer Earth.

293
00:19:38,350 --> 00:19:40,930
What're you doing living a leisurely life as a kept pet?!

294
00:19:41,140 --> 00:19:42,940
What's the idea of getting them riled up?

295
00:19:44,290 --> 00:19:46,240
I failed to convince them, huh?

296
00:19:46,240 --> 00:19:49,620
Well, that's okay.  At least I got to touch some cuddly balls of flesh.

297
00:19:49,620 --> 00:19:51,050
What're you so happy about?!

298
00:19:51,050 --> 00:19:53,010
What is it with you and cuddly balls of flesh?!

299
00:19:53,360 --> 00:19:54,550
We have no choice.

300
00:19:54,550 --> 00:19:56,710
Now that it's come to this, I'll draw them to me.

301
00:19:56,930 --> 00:19:59,530
During that time, Leader, you go to the old man's place.

302
00:19:59,530 --> 00:20:01,330
Zura, you'd do all that?

303
00:20:02,490 --> 00:20:06,380
I don't want to see cuddly balls of flesh fighting among themselves.

304
00:20:07,930 --> 00:20:09,700
Take care of the rest, Leader!

305
00:20:12,800 --> 00:20:16,470
I have discovered Bushido in a death surrounded by cuddly balls of flesh!

306
00:20:19,610 --> 00:20:22,200
All right, come at me, you cuddly balls of flesh!

307
00:20:24,510 --> 00:20:28,580
With your cuddly balls of flesh...at me...

308
00:20:30,790 --> 00:20:33,220
They ignored him!

309
00:20:38,220 --> 00:20:40,220
[Special Prizes Stefan Goods!! A chance to win 2 weeks in a row!!]

310
00:20:39,040 --> 00:20:40,640
Good grief...

311
00:20:40,640 --> 00:20:42,800
My body's not gonna last if this keeps on.

312
00:20:43,120 --> 00:20:47,840
If you're going to die, Dad, hurry up and get on with it. I mean really.

313
00:21:12,120 --> 00:21:13,850
This is no good.

314
00:21:17,960 --> 00:21:20,000
Time for my walk.

315
00:21:22,100 --> 00:21:23,630
[To be continued]

316
00:22:52,100 --> 00:22:55,600
[Tell me! Ginpachi Sensei!]

317
00:22:52,820 --> 00:22:55,600
Tell me! Ginpachi Sensei!

318
00:22:55,670 --> 00:23:00,650
Okay, today, we have a letter from someone a bit unusual. I'll read it now.

319
00:23:01,240 --> 00:23:04,390
It's a question from Amachi Hideaki of Tokyo.

320
00:23:04,700 --> 00:23:07,220
This is about something that happened a while back.

321
00:23:07,220 --> 00:23:09,780
When I saw an ending where Kagura was running along the beach in Summer,

322
00:23:09,780 --> 00:23:12,620
I wondered about something, so I wrote this letter.

323
00:23:12,620 --> 00:23:15,850
If I'm not mistaken, Kagura is an Amanto belonging to the Yato Clan,

324
00:23:15,850 --> 00:23:17,960
who are supposed to be vulnerable to sunlight.

325
00:23:17,960 --> 00:23:20,990
Basically, wasn't it a given that she always uses a parasol?

326
00:23:21,690 --> 00:23:26,030
I draw a lot of manga myself, and often forget to draw in the parasol.

327
00:23:26,030 --> 00:23:27,470
But is it all right to do that?

328
00:23:27,470 --> 00:23:30,090
It bothers me so much, I can't get on with my manuscript.

329
00:23:30,570 --> 00:23:32,640
Okay, here's the straight answer.

330
00:23:33,000 --> 00:23:34,400
Yes, I do remember.

331
00:23:34,670 --> 00:23:36,940
It's the one where the voice actress of Kagura said

332
00:23:36,940 --> 00:23:39,630
"Who is this cute girl who appears in the ending?"

333
00:23:39,630 --> 00:23:40,790
when she first saw it, right?

334
00:23:41,070 --> 00:23:45,720
That certainly was Kagura running energetically under the sun with her skin exposed.

335
00:23:46,070 --> 00:23:47,730
But she's fine.

336
00:23:47,730 --> 00:23:49,630
Huh? Why is she fine, you ask?

337
00:23:50,100 --> 00:23:51,670
Okay.

338
00:23:51,670 --> 00:23:53,590
Actually, that was filmed in studio.

339
00:23:54,320 --> 00:23:56,770
Adults play so dirty, don't they?

340
00:23:57,100 --> 00:23:59,960
They explain everything that's not going their way after the fact.

341
00:24:00,260 --> 00:24:03,080
Well, then, Amachi! Don't worry so much about details.

342
00:24:03,080 --> 00:24:05,100
Have a manuscript by tomorrow.

343
00:24:05,100 --> 00:24:09,680
